Ultramar gets Total shareholder okay . Ultramar Diamond Shamrock Corp said Tuesday that shareholders of Total Petroleum ( North America ) Ltd had approved the acquisition of the company at a special meeting in Calgary , Alberta , Canada . Additionally , the companies said in a joint statement that Ultramar is working to provide the Federal Trade Commission with added information that the FTC had asked for last week . The two petroleum refining and marketing companies announced in April a definitive pact for Ultramar to acquire Total in a deal valued at $ 811 million , including the assumption of $ 414 million of Total Petroleum debt . The deal converts each outstanding Total Petroleum share into 0 . 322 per share of Ultramar common stock . Completion remains subject to government approvals in Canada and the U . S . 
